Neil:  Ouch!  I got a bug in my eye.

Bob:  Let me see.

Neil:  I can't see.  I got a bug in my eye!

Bob:  Not you see.  Me see!

Neil:  I 'm sure you can, but you don't have a bug in your eye.

Bob:  I wanna see the bug.

Neil:  How can you see the bug if it's in my eye?  It's in my eye and I can't see it, because I can't see anything with a damn bug in my eye.

Bob:  I wanna see your eye to see if I can see the bug.

Neil:  Okay, look at my eye.

Bob:  I don't see anything.

Neil:  Well, I know there's a bug in there.

Bob:  No, I don't see anything.  There's a bug in my eye!

In the headlines:  "Comet May Have Caused Mass Extinction 250 Million Years Ago."  

I hope this makes people realize just how dangerous the chemicals in household cleaning products can be.  Imagine the carnage.  T-Rex blown away by Windex.  Raptors wiped out by Pledge...and just how many neanderthals lay dead with yellow lips and an empty bottle of Mr. Clean clenched in their hairy palms?  Oh, the horror.

We all know Men in Black (MIB) protect us from aliens.  But, if you really think about it, the color of what people wear pretty much dictates what they do.

Men in Blue - Protect us from crime
Men in Red - Protect us from fire
Men in Green - Protect us from other countries on land
Men in White - Protect us from other countries at sea
Men in Yellow - Protect us from radiation
Men in Orange - Prisoners
Men in Brown - Deliver packages
Men in Purple - Minnesota Vikings
Men in Silver - Pilot spaceships
Men in Pink - Well, you get the idea...

Question is, what color's your shirt?
